ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, we develop a one-pot room temperature method for the synthesis of the orange-emitting CDs (O-CDs) based on Schiff base reaction crosslinking between triethylenetetramine and methyl-p-benzoquinone (Scheme 1
                     ). The as-prepared O-CDs have an excitation-dependent emission, and the maximum emission wavelength is at about 580 nm when exciting by 460 nm excitation light. Importantly, the relative quantum yield (rhodamine 6G as a reference) of the O-CDs reaches 6.56%, giving a bright orange FL emission. Moreover, the orange FL emission of O-CDs can be efficiently quenched based on the strong inner filter effect (IFE). Further experimental results show that the emission intensity ratio (F/F
                     0) of O-CDs is linearly correlated with VB12 concentration from 0.05 to 200 μM. The presented nanoprobe shows good photostability and high sensitivity with a low detection limit of 10 nM towards VB12.
